String: It is an objetc that can store a sequence of characters enclosed 
by double quotes. 

"Welcome to String!!"

UTF-16bit enconding 

Immutable - can't be changed/modified

heap memory - 

Declaration ways
i)String literal - stored statically - in String Constant pool
ii)New keyword - stored dynamically - in Heap memory

String st="hello"
st="hi"
String st1="hello"

String st=new String("Hello");

Classes and Interfaces:
i)CharSequence Interface
ii)String  - Immutable
iii)StringBuffer - mutable & thread safe
iv)StringBuilder - mutable & non thread safe
v)StringTokenizer - It is used to break a string into tokens



Autoboxing and Unboxing:

data conversion - primitive <-> non-primitive

Types conversion - manually(programatically)/automatically(compiler)




Autoboxing: Automatic conversion of primitive -> wrapper object (compiler)

int a=5;
Integer obj=a;  //Autoboxing


Unboxing: Automatic conversion of Wrapper object into primitive.


Integer obj=5;
int a=obj;     //Unboxing


Wrapper classes: Wrapper classes are objects that wrap primitive data
into a class;


Integer, Double, Float, Boolean, Character, Short, Byte, Long 

 


















